The Nigeria Centre for Disease Control, NCDC, has updated the list of state emergency numbers as Coronavirus (COVID-19) cases in Nigeria hit 254. NCDC disclosed this in a tweet on its official Twitter page on Wednesday morning. “COVID-19 in Nigeria. We have updated the list of State Ministry of Health emergency numbers. If you require testing: 1. Contact your STATE through these numbers 2. Provide relevant details 3. Stay isolated & wait for further advice,” NCDC tweeted. DAILY POST recalls that NCDC had earlier in the month updated the list of state emergency numbers. See list below… 